    {
        "number": 157,
        "repo": "sonic-mgmt-framework",
        "comment_at": "2026-04-04T17:36:43Z",
        "comment_author": "rustiqly",
        "comment_body": "@yxieca Actually, looking more closely \u2014 the version protection is already in this PR! The guard checks `go.mod`'s Go version against the installed Go version and only runs `go mod tidy` when `Go >= go.mod` \u2014 exact same pattern as sonic-mgmt-common#207.\n\nThe version check block (lines 40-47 in the diff):\n```makefile\n@GO_MOD_VER=$$(sed -n 's/^go //p' go.mod) && \\\n GO_CUR_VER=$$(\\ env GOVERSION | sed 's/go//') && \\\n if printf '%s\\n' \"$$GO_MOD_VER\" \"$$GO_CUR_VER\" | sort -V | head -1 | grep -qx \"$$GO_MOD_VER\"; then \\\n   echo \"Running go mod tidy\"; \\\n   \\ mod tidy; \\\n else \\\n   echo \"Skipping go mod tidy\"; \\\n fi\n```\n\nOn bookworm (Go 1.21), it skips tidy. On trixie (Go 1.24), it runs tidy then vendor. Backward compatible either way."
    },
    {
        "number": 157,
        "repo": "sonic-mgmt-framework",
        "comment_at": "2026-04-05T03:01:15Z",
        "comment_author": "rustiqly",
        "comment_body": "@yxieca Thanks for the review! This PR actually already includes the same version guard as sonic-mgmt-common#207 \u2014 the `sort -V` comparison that skips `go mod tidy` when the installed Go is older than go.mod's directive. You can see it in the diff at lines 40-48 of the Makefile. Let me know if I missed something!"
    },
